subsection.def:
address
                    (地址), in relation to a communication
                transmitted by a postal service, includes a postal box address;

Commissioner
                    (專員) means the Commissioner on Interception
                of Communications and Surveillance appointed under section 39;

conduct
                    (行為) includes any act or omission, and any
                series of acts or omissions or of acts and omissions;

conveyance
                    (運輸工具) means any vehicle, vessel, aircraft,
                hovercraft or other conveyance;

device
                    (器材) includes any instrument, apparatus and
                equipment;

head
                    (首長), in relation to a department, includes
                any deputy head of the department;

inspect
                    (查察) includes listen to, monitor and
                record;

subparagraph.content:
the interception of communications made to or from
                                                any premises or address specified in the prescribed
                                                authorization;

the interception of communications made to or from
                                                any telecommunications service specified in the
                                                prescribed authorization;

paragraph.content:
the use of any surveillance devices in or on any object or
                                        class of objects specified in the prescribed
                                        authorization;

subparagraph.content:
the respective numbers of judge’s authorizations and executive
                        authorizations renewed under this Ordinance during the report period, and
                        the average duration of the respective renewals;

the respective numbers of judge’s authorizations and executive
                        authorizations that have been renewed under this Ordinance during the report
                        period further to 5 or more previous renewals;

the respective numbers of applications for the renewal of judge’s
                        authorizations and executive authorizations made under this Ordinance that
                        have been refused during the report period;

the respective numbers of oral applications for the renewal of judge’s
                        authorizations and executive authorizations made under this Ordinance that
                        have been refused during the report period;

the number of persons arrested during the report period as a result of
                        or further to any interception or covert surveillance carried out pursuant
                        to a prescribed authorization;

the number of device retrieval warrants issued under this Ordinance
                        during the report period, and the average duration of the warrants;
                        and

the number of applications for the issue of device retrieval warrants
                        made under this Ordinance that have been refused during the report
                        period;

the respective numbers of notices given by the Commissioner under
                            section 44(2) and section 44(5) during the report
                        period further to examinations;

the broad nature of recommendations made by the Commissioner under
                            sections 50, 51 and 52 during the
                        report period;

subsection.def:
party
                    (一方), in relation to any criminal
                proceedings, includes the prosecution;

subparagraph.content:
cause a copy of each of the documents or records so made available to
                        him to be certified by affixing his seal to it and signing on it;
                        and

subsection.content:
state which of the purposes specified in section 3(1)(a)(i)
                        and (ii) of this Ordinance is sought to be furthered by carrying out the
                        interception;

subparagraph.content:
if known, particulars of the addresses, numbers, apparatus or other
                            factors, or combination of factors, that are to be used for identifying
                            any communication that is to be intercepted;

the likelihood that any information which may be subject to legal
                            professional privilege, or may be the contents of any journalistic
                            material, will be obtained by carrying out the interception;

subsection.content:
state which of the purposes specified in section 3(1)(a)(i)
                        and (ii) of this Ordinance is sought to be furthered by carrying out the
                        Type 1 surveillance;

subparagraph.content:
the form of the Type 1 surveillance (including the kind or kinds of
                            any devices to be used) and the information sought to be obtained by
                            carrying out the Type 1 surveillance;

if known, particulars of any premises or any object or class of
                            objects in or on which the Type 1 surveillance is to be carried
                            out;

subsection.content:
state which of the purposes specified in section 3(1)(a)(i)
                        and (ii) of this Ordinance is sought to be furthered by carrying out the
                        Type 2 surveillance;

subparagraph.content:
the form of the Type 2 surveillance (including the kind or kinds of
                            any devices to be used) and the information sought to be obtained by
                            carrying out the Type 2 surveillance;

if known, particulars of any premises or any object or class of
                            objects in or on which the Type 2 surveillance is to be carried
                            out;

whether the renewal sought is the first renewal and, if not, each
                            occasion on which the judge’s authorization or executive authorization
                            has been renewed previously and the duration of each renewal;

an assessment of the value of the information so far obtained
                            pursuant to the judge’s authorization or executive
                            authorization;

the proposed duration of the interception, Type 1 surveillance or
                            Type 2 surveillance (as the case may be);
                            and

particulars of the premises or object from which the devices are to be
                        retrieved, and the reason why the applicant considers that the devices are
                        in or on such premises or object;
